Note：GMT time can only be got after accessing to the Internet.

This page is used to set the router’s system time, you can choose to either set the time manually, or get the GMT time from the Internet and the system will automatically connect to NTP server to synchronize the time.

Note: The time information will be lost after you power off the router, and when you next time access to the Internet, the router will obtain the GMT time automatically. You should firstly access to the Internet to obtain the GMT time or set the time manually on this page, and then the time settings in other functions can be effective.

message.msgid: Please enter the correct DDNS information
message.msgstr: Please enter the correct DDNS information!

DDNS (Dynamic DNS) Service allows you to assign a fixed domain name for dynamic WAN IP so as to monitor your LAN Web, TCP/IP FTP or other TCP/IP .Before setting the DDNS, you need to click <Sign up> and go to the corresponding website to register a domain name.
DDNS Service: Select the corresponding DDNS service provider from the drop-down menu and enter the username, password and hostname to enable the service.

Click "Backup" to back up the current configuration to the corresponding directory and form a system configured backup file.In the same way, you only need to click "Browse" to select the configured file from the corresponding directory, click "Restore" and restart the router after finishing, the system configuration you need can be restored.

The device will restart automatically! The IP will update to 192.168.2.1, and password to admin, if the web page hasn’t been refreshed, please refresh your computer’s network configuration and log on again.

message.msgid: By upgrading the router software, you get new features.
message.msgstr: By upgrading the router’ software, you’ll get new features.

Old password :Enter the old password .The router’s default password is admin.(Note: Password can not be resumed once it is forgotten or lost. If you have forgot or lost your password, you must reset the router to factory default).

Confirm password: Re-enter the new password to confirm.
